traits.description: Timmy enjoys the feeling of freedom that comes from being nude. he can handle clothing, but will be happier without it.
traits.name: nudist

traits.description: Timmy gets a rush from hurting people, and never minds the sight of blood or death. he is four times as likely to start a social fight as others.
traits.name: bloodlust

traits.description: Timmy is an exceptionally agreeable and giving person. he never insults others and will sometimes offer kind words to brighten the moods of those around him. he also never judges people by their appearance. his agreeableness also makes him more likely to conform to prevailing opinions.
traits.name: kind

traits.description: Timmy has no empathy. The suffering of others doesn't bother him at all. he doesn't mind if others are butchered, left unburied, imprisoned, or sold to slavery - unless it affects him. he also feels no mood boost from socializing.
traits.name: psychopath

traits.description: Timmy was taught that eating human meat is wrong and horrible. But one time, long ago, he tried it... and he liked it.
traits.name: cannibal

traits.description: Timmy always says exactly what's on his mind, especially if it's bugging him. That tends to rub people the wrong way.
traits.name: abrasive

traits.description: Timmy is too smart for his own good. he learns everything much faster than everyone, but can be quite eccentric.
traits.name: toosmart

traits.description: Timmy likes to fight up close and personal. his accuracy is greatly increased in melee combat, but he'll be very unhappy if asked to carry a ranged weapon.
traits.name: brawler

traits.description: For Timmy, there's something exciting about getting hurt. he doesn't know why, he's just wired differently.
traits.name: masochist

traits.description:
Timmy likes to be up during the night, and sleep during the day.

he gets a mood bonus if awake at night (23h-6h) and mood loss if awake during the day (11h-18h).

he doesn't get a mood penalty for being in the dark.
traits.name: nightowl

traits.description: Timmy needs a really impressive bedroom. he gets a mood loss if he doesn't get what he wants.
traits.name: greedy

traits.description: For Timmy, it's degrading to have a less impressive bedroom than someone else. he gets a mood loss if any colonist has a more impressive bedroom.
traits.name: jealous

traits.description: Timmy has forsaken physical comforts and enjoyments in favor of a simple, pure lifestyle. he will become unhappy if he has a bedroom that's too impressive. he also dislikes fancy food and prefers to eat raw. he never judges others by their appearance.
traits.name: ascetic

traits.description: Timmy is romantically attracted to people of his own gender.
traits.name: gay

traits.description: Timmy is romantically attracted to both men and women.
traits.name: bisexual

traits.description: Timmy has no sexual attraction to anyone at all.
traits.name: asexual

traits.description: Timmy's voice has a particularly grating, nasal quality to it, and he tends to talk in barked, garbled phrases. This predisposes others to dislike him.
traits.name: annoyingvoice

traits.description: Timmy breathes heavily all the time, and sweats constantly. People find it creepy.
traits.name: creepybreathing

traits.description: Timmy loves fire. he will never extinguish fires. To relieve stress, he will occasionally go on random fire starting sprees. This happens more often if his mood is low.
traits.name: pyromaniac

traits.description: Timmy is weak and cowardly. Even a little pain will immobilize him.
traits.name: wimp

traits.description: Timmy has remarkable kinesthetic intelligence. he seems to dance around danger with preternatural grace.
traits.name: nimble

traits.description: Timmy has a knack for learning. he picks things up much faster than others.
traits.name: fastlearner

traits.description: Timmy is slow on the uptake. he learns much slower than others.
traits.name: slowlearner

traits.description: Timmy has no need to experience the outdoors or light. he will never feel cooped up or get cabin fever, no matter how long he stays inside, and is not bothered by darkness.
traits.name: undergrounder

traits.description: Timmy feels limited in his feeble human body. he often dreams of being enhanced by artificial body parts.
traits.name: bodymodder

traits.description: Timmy believes the human body is limited for a reason. To him, artificial body parts are unethical and disgusting.
traits.name: bodypurist

traits.description: Timmy really dislikes and distrusts men.
traits.name: misandrist

traits.description: Timmy really dislikes and distrusts women.
traits.name: misogynist

traits.description: Timmy has a fantastic memory for detail. he will learn new skills slightly faster than other people.
traits.name: greatmemory

traits.description: Timmy has thick skin, dense flesh, and durable bones. he takes much less damage than other people from the same blows. he is extremely hard to kill.
traits.name: tough

traits.description: Timmy feels alienated and misunderstood by other human beings. he will have a constant mood debuff, but gain a chance (50%) to get a creativity inspiration after a mental break.
traits.name: torturedartist

traits.description: Timmy's life revolves around food. he gets hungry quickly, and will occasionally be overcome with the urge to eat ravenously, even when not hungry.
traits.name: gourmand

traits.description: Timmy doesn't need as much sleep as the average person. Whether he's sleeping on a bed or on the ground, he will be fully rested in about two thirds the usual time.
traits.name: quicksleeper

traits.description: Timmy is always falling behind the group whenever he goes anywhere.
traits.name: slowpoke

traits.description: Timmy likes to be where he's going. he walks quicker than most people.
traits.name: fastwalker

traits.description: Timmy always moves with a sense of urgency - so much so that others often fail to keep up.
traits.name: jogger

traits.description: Timmy is utterly fascinated with chemical sources of enjoyment. Consuming recreational drugs will create a good mood, while abstaining will lead to increasing frustration over time and possibly drug binges. he will ignore directives to not use recreational drugs, and will consume more than a normal person.
traits.name: chemicalfascination

traits.description: Timmy has an unusual interest in chemical sources of enjoyment. Consuming recreational drugs will create a good mood, while abstaining will lead to increasing frustration over time and possible drug binges. he will ignore directives to not use recreational drugs, and will consume more than a normal person.
traits.name: chemicalinterest

traits.description: Timmy abhors the idea of gaining pleasure from chemicals. he strictly avoids alcohol and recreational drugs.
stats: Binging on drug mental state disabled.
Binging on drug mental state disabled.
Binging on drug mental state disabled.
Binging on drug mental state disabled.

traits.name: teetotaler

traits.description: Timmy is just naturally upbeat about his situation, pretty much all the time, no matter what it is.
traits.name: sanguine

traits.description: Timmy is naturally optimistic about life. It's hard to get him down.
traits.name: optimist

traits.description: Timmy tends to look on the bad side of life.
traits.name: pessimist

traits.description: Timmy is perenially unhappy. he has trouble sustaining a good mood even when everything is fine.
traits.name: depressive

traits.description: Timmy's will is an iron shield. he keeps going through thick and thin, when others broke down long before.
traits.name: iron-willed

traits.description: Timmy is mentally tough and won't break down under stresses that would crack most people.
traits.name: steadfast

traits.description: Timmy tends to crack under pressure.
traits.name: nervous

traits.description: Timmy is on a hair-trigger all the time. he is the first to break in any tough situation.
traits.name: volatile

traits.description: Timmy likes to have things squared away. he will work harder than most to attain this state of affairs, but his nerves can get the better of him.
traits.name: neurotic

traits.description: Timmy feels constantly nervous about everything that has to get done. he will work extremely hard to attain this state of affairs, but his nerves can easily get the better of him.
traits.name: veryneurotic

traits.description: Timmy has an easy time staying on-task and focused, and gets things done much faster than the average person.
traits.name: industrious

traits.description: Timmy is a natural hard worker and will finish tasks faster than most.
traits.name: hardworker

traits.description: Timmy is a little bit lazy.
traits.name: lazy

traits.description: Timmy loves idleness and hates anything productive. he moves slowly and rarely stays focused on a task.
traits.name: slothful

traits.description: Timmy's mind is like a psychic tuning fork. he is extremely sensitive to psychic phenomena.
traits.name: psychicallyhypersensitive

traits.description: Timmy's mind is unusually sensitive to psychic phenomena.
traits.name: psychicallysensitive

traits.description: Timmy's mind is psychically out of tune with others. he isn't as affected by psychic phenomena.
traits.name: psychicallydull

traits.description: Timmy's mind works on a psychic frequency different from everyone else. he just isn't affected by psychic phenomena.
traits.name: psychicallydeaf

traits.description: Timmy takes more time to aim when shooting. he shoots less often than others, but with more accuracy.
traits.name: carefulshooter

traits.description: Pew! Pew! Pew! Timmy just likes pulling the trigger. he shoots faster than others, but less accurately.
traits.name: trigger-happy

traits.description: Timmy is exceptionally beautiful, with an exotic-yet-familiar facial structure and an arresting gaze. People are attracted to him before he even opens his mouth.
traits.name: beautiful

traits.description: Timmy has a pretty face, which predisposes people to like him.
traits.name: pretty

traits.description: Timmy is somewhat ugly. This subtly repels others during social interactions.
traits.name: ugly

traits.description: Timmy is staggeringly ugly. his face looks like a cross between a drawing by an untalented child, a malformed fetus in a jar of formaldehyde, and a piece of modern art. Others must exert conscious effort to look at him while conversing.
traits.name: staggeringlyugly

traits.description: Timmy has a naturally powerful immune system. he will gain immunity much faster than a normal person would, and can survive illnesses that would kill others.
traits.name: super-immune

traits.description: Timmy has an awful immune system. he gets sick more often than usual, frequently with illnesses that nobody in the colony has been afflicted by.
traits.name: sickly

traits.description: Timmy always saw their body as nothing more than a vessel for their mind. he does not care about the gender, age or looks of a body.
traits.name: freemind

traits.description: Timmy hates and distrusts xenos. They see them as little more than animals.
traits.name: xenophobe

traits.description: Timmy thinks aliens are exotic and interesting. They would love to get to know them more and wouldn't mind forming relationships with them.
traits.name: xenophile

traits.description: Timmy hates the sight of the human body. he will be extremely unhappy when naked, more displeased than usual in tattered or worn-out clothing, and dislike the sight of other naked people.
traits.name: prude

traits.description: Timmy finds it difficult to sleep because of his condition. he will prioritize sleep less, wake up sooner, and get less rest from sleeping.
traits.name: insomniac

traits.description: Timmy has a big heart and gets very emotional. he loves helping people, and abhors violence and injustice. he is more affected by these things than others.
traits.name: bleedingheart

traits.description: Timmy is always a critic when it comes to food. he expects to be fed well and will complain if his meals aren't up to par.
traits.name: gourmet

traits.description: Timmy is more prone to random mood swings, which can be more severe than normal for others.
traits.name: unstable

traits.description: Timmy is unabashedly lecherous and a thoughtless heartbreaker. he will hit on anyone he desires with no regard for the consequences.
traits.name: lecher

traits.description: Timmy is romantically needy and won't be happy unless in a relationship. he will be devastated by infidelity and breakups.
traits.name: codependent

traits.description: Timmy loves to be outside. he gets a mood bonus when there is no roof over his head.
traits.name: outdoorsy

traits.description: Timmy likes the rain. he gets a mood bonus when it's pouring outside, especially if he gets to go out in it.
traits.name: pluviophile

traits.description: Timmy has eyes, either through gene modding or random mutation, that are extremely light-sensitive. he finds bright light extremely painful and indoor lighting bothersome, and will be happiest in the dark.
traits.name: photosensitive

traits.description: Timmy loves to party! his mere presence inspires more parties in the colony, because everyone enjoys partying with him.
traits.name: socialite

traits.description: Timmy has seen enough violence and death that it no longer shocks him like it used to.
traits.name: desensitized

traits.description: Timmy sleeps like a rock, never bothered by adverse sleeping conditions, but is difficult to wake up.
traits.name: heavysleeper

traits.description: Timmy doesn't see any problem with having multiple partners. he doesn't mind if his partner romances other people, but will be less happy in a restraining, monogamous relationship.
traits.name: polyamorous

traits.description: Timmy sees people for what they are on the inside, not the outside. he doesn't judge others for their appearances.
traits.name: open-minded

traits.description: Timmy isn't a very active person. he isn't very physically fit, but he enjoys sitting around all day working on things.
traits.name: sedentary

traits.description: Timmy just talks and talks and talks... and talks. he tends to have longer conversations than most, because he can't seem to end them.
traits.name: chatty

traits.description: Timmy has been blessed by the Mechanicus to be overall better than regular humans at all tasked related to research, craft and mining. he is blessed for a harsh working environment.

data.mod: Astra Militarum Imperial Guard Core Mod v2.3

traits.name: imperial-mechanicus

traits.description: Timmy has been blessed by the Emperor to be overall better than regular humans at all tasked related to combat to better serve the Emperor against Chaos. he is blessed with general combat excellence.

data.mod: Astra Militarum Imperial Guard Core Mod v2.3

traits.name: imperial-astramilitarum

traits.description: Timmy has been trained by the Officio Assassinorum to be a surgical tool to serve the Emperor against Chaos. he is blessed for combat excellence at range.

data.mod: Astra Militarum Imperial Guard Core Mod v2.3

traits.name: imperial-assassinorum

traits.description: Timmy has been trained by the Inquisition as the secret police of the Imperium responsible for guarding the souls of humanity. he is blessed by the Inquisition with a many varied skills.

data.mod: Astra Militarum Imperial Guard Core Mod v2.3

traits.name: imperial-inquisition

traits.description: Timmy has been training in the arts of all medicine to help their fellow imperial citizens. he is blessed with medical excellence.

data.mod: Astra Militarum Imperial Guard Core Mod v2.3

traits.name: imperial-medic

traits.description: Timmy has been blessed by the Emperor be the pinnacle of Human Warfare as one of his Chosen Astarte in the fight against Chaos. he is blessed with the Astarte Trait.

data.mod: Astra Militarum Imperial Guard Core Mod v2.3

traits.name: imperial-astarte

traits.description: Timmy is a follower of the Imperial cult. Though life may seem arduous, complicated and finally with much suffering, NAME will carry on in the knowledge, that the Emperor has a plan. And however long it may take to unfold, the Imperium of Man will prevail until such time.
traits.name: imperialendurance

traits.description: Timmy is a follower of Ynnead. The spiral towards death is the only way to free the Eldar.

traits.description: Timmy is a follower of Cegorach, the Laughing God.

traits.description: Timmy is on the Path of the Warrior, embodying aspects of Khaela Mensha Khaine.

traits.description: Timmy is always in a good mood, for Papa Nurgle is looking after he.

traits.name: eldarmastery

traits.description: Timmy follows the idea that all beings should strive to ensure the greatest good for the greatest number of beings in the galaxy.
traits.name: utalitarianphilosophy

traits.description: Timmy is an Orkoid, meaning HIS life evolves around seemingly mindless bloodshed.
traits.name: orkmindedness

traits.description: Timmy does not believe in divinity. There are no gods among the stars, only cruel and powerful forces worthy of contempt.
traits.name: atheist

traits.description: Timmy strongly believes in the divine.
traits.name: ferventbeliever

traits.description: Timmy's life is dedicated to the divine and believes are worth to go to war for.

traits.description: Timmy walks under the gaze of Ynnead, the Aeldari god of death.

traits.name: aspiringsaint

traits.description: This individual was selected by the Emperor to fulfill a purpose. he is close to fulfilling that goal.
traits.name: aspiringsaint

traits.description: Timmy has braved he trials and has become an Imperial saint walking among mere mortals.

traits.description: Timmy enjoys the solitude and tranquility inherent to long fishing sessions. he will prefer fishing above other activities.
traits.name: fisherman

traits.description: Timmy has Solid exoskeleton, he takes much less damage than other Anties from the same blows.
traits.name: solidexoskeleton

traits.description: Timmy hates fire. he will refuse to get close to fire to put it out.
traits.name: pyrophobia

traits.description: Timmy tends to occasionally allow their mind to drift, even in the middle of working.
traits.name: absent-minded

traits.description: Timmy has a loose screw or two, a small trade off for being naturally scientifically inclined.
traits.name: eccentric

traits.description: Timmy strives for perfection in his work. They will naturally produce better quality products at the expense of time. However, making a low quality product will upset them. Additionally, they may very rarely quit a project mid attempt if they don't like the direction its going in.
traits.name: perfectionist

traits.description: While fully capable of warfare in theory, Timmy's fight or flight instincts heavily lean towards flight, and he will try to hide or run as a first priority.
traits.name: coward

traits.description: Timmy has a higher mental and physical fortitude compared to most and can more readily adapt to harsh environments in the rimworlds.
traits.name: brave

traits.description: Minor bruises and scrapes plague Timmy all too often, mostly due to uncoordinated tripping or falling.
traits.name: clumsy

traits.description: Timmy loves the brightness and heat of a dry summer day. They don't mind working up a sweat or sleeping in the warmth either.
traits.name: heatinclined

traits.description: Timmy loves the overcast and cold of a brisk winter night. They don't mind getting chilly or sleeping in the cold either.
traits.name: coldinclined

traits.description: A bomb could go off next to Timmy while they sleep and they'd continue to do so. They can't be bothered to defend the colony mid catnap, either.
traits.name: heavysleeper

traits.description: Timmy is naturally hygenic and organized. They will not track in dirt or throw trash anywhere, and feel happy while cleaning.
traits.name: neat

traits.description: Timmy is sloppy naturally and leaves trash and dirt everywhere it seems. At least they're not much bothered by messes.
traits.name: slob

traits.description: Timmy has problems taking breaks or resting mid job. he will continue to work even sacrificing their health or sleep.
traits.name: workaholic

traits.description: Timmy has never felt nausea in his life. Throwing up or food poisoning is foreign to him.
traits.name: ironstomach

traits.description: Timmy can't stand mistreatment of animals. he will feel happier being nuzzled or being a master to a bonded animal, but will be more deeply crushed when not master of a bonded animal or seeing one die. They also refuse to butcher.
traits.name: animallover

traits.description: Timmy believes deeply in human superiority. Killing animals will please them and the colony losing an animal is a cherry on top according to them.
traits.name: animalhater

traits.description: Whether because they're a bit chunky or because they shift their weight oddly, Timmy has broken a few chairs in their time and is likely to break more.
traits.name: big-boned

traits.description: Timmy only plays by their own rules, and will roll their eyes and take it easy while doing any task they've been forced to do.
traits.name: rebel

traits.description: Timmy needs clear instructions on how, and when to do certain things and will only work at a normal speed when being forced to do something.
traits.name: submissive

traits.description: Timmy is fueled by spite. They can't stand walking on the same soil as their rivals and will be elated by news of their life ending.
traits.name: vengeful

traits.description: Whether by past trauma or fear of change, Timmy rejects modernity. They may randomly punch or attack mechanical devices and refuse to learn or research anything about them. They also love killing mechanoids.
traits.name: technophobe

traits.description: Timmy always recalls the good times and lives to party, any party attended will be remembered for many times longer than most.
traits.name: fun-loving

traits.description: Timmy has hindered mental capacities. While slow to learn and hard to speak with, they tend to be much happier naturally.
traits.name: dunce

traits.description: Timmy learned a specific move in melee combat which allows them to disarm opponents and will use it frequently.
traits.name: martialartist

traits.description: Timmy believes they belong in high society, and loves nothing more than critiquing art and brushing elbows with royalty.
traits.name: snob

traits.description: Sour stomach plagues Timmy any time they're around too much blood or rotting corpses. Vomiting is just part of life for him.
traits.name: squeamish

traits.description: Timmy feels naturally anxious, but especially from social situations. They will not attend any gatherings and may occasionally need alone time in their room to breathe.
traits.name: anxious

traits.description: No amount of lovin' is enough lovin' for Timmy. he will tend to jump from partner to partner and tumble between the sheets with them frequently.
traits.name: insatiable

traits.description: Timmy refuses to give their body to anybody but their spouse and would never fathom initiating a divorce. They also hate being nude much more than other pawns.
traits.name: prude

traits.description: An armchair and flatscreen is all Timmy needs to be happy. Even reruns or ancient commercials are entertaining to them, they will never grow bored of television and tend to watch it more, as well as feel pleased after doing so.
traits.name: couchpotato

traits.description: Timmy is mad for all things feline. They will naturally gravitate towards bonding with cats, however they're not a fan of dogs.
traits.name: catperson

traits.description: Timmy is mad for all things canine. They will naturally gravitate towards bonding with dogs, however they're not a fan of cats.
traits.name: dogperson

traits.description: Timmy is a natural scientist. They research much faster and recall things better. However, they'll be upset without a laboratory dedicated to their work and tend to stress out more frequently.
traits.name: prodigy

traits.description: Timmy believes animals are integral to the way society and life functions from furry friends to sources of food. They love having as many as possible and are particularly good at taming and training them.
traits.name: menagerist

traits.description: The sea calls to Timmy. he feels happier just being near the ocean or a deep river.
traits.name: oceanlover

traits.description: The mountains call to Timmy. he feels happier just being near a large mountain.
traits.name: mountainlover

traits.description: Timmy has a twisted secret. he treats organ harvesting like a sick experiment, and does not even blink at the idea. While harvesting one will make them happy, going too long without giving in to their compulsion will upset them.
traits.name: madsurgeon

traits.description: Timmy is supposedly a hand-to-hand combat specialist, but only when inebriated. They claim to become more talented the more drunk they are.
traits.name: drunkenmaster

traits.description: Timmy is compulsed to steal and take things that don't belong to them, even if it means angering the other party.
traits.name: kleptomaniac

traits.description: Smokeleaf culture is just part of life for Timmy. he absolutely adores smokeleaf and would rather die before giving it up.
traits.name: stoner

traits.description: Alcohol culture is just part of life for Timmy. he absolutely adores booze and would rather die before giving it up.
traits.name: lush

traits.description: Timmy loves to travel and does so swiftly, but can grow upset if they haven't done so in a while. They are also quite adept at foraging while traveling.
traits.name: wanderlust

traits.description: Timmy is never really asleep or awake. he is almost zombie like, lurching along and working very slowly, and will only sleep once every three days or so.
traits.name: insomniac

traits.description: Timmy has grown tired of the world and needs to be constantly distracted to stop dark thoughts. his bleak personality is a big downer and therefore it is very hard to become friends with them.
traits.name: worldweary

traits.description: Timmy is hardened through what can only be presumed as old emotional trauma. They feel absolutely nothing from lost animals, colonists, family, prisoners or dead bodies.
traits.name: desensitized

traits.description: Only the finest of culinary creations may grace the lips of Timmy. They feel neutral towards mundane meals, but will laud and savour lavish meals down to the last bite.
traits.name: refinedpalate

traits.description: Whether through studying ancient manuscripts or years of scholastic pursuit Timmy is surprisingly well read on a variety of topics, particularly science and medical practice.
traits.name: academian

traits.description: Timmy strongly believes infrastucture rules all and is a natural born stoneworker.
traits.name: groundbreaker

traits.description: In the eyes of Timmy food is art, their culinary creations are incredibly beautiful, amazing to taste, and almost always safe to eat.
traits.name: gastronomist

traits.description: Flora and fauna are both vital to Timmy. They use all parts of plants and animals and strongly appreciate mother Gaia's blessings.
traits.name: ecologist

traits.description: Timmy has an eye for silver and a tongue made from it. They believe their products are the best products and he will likely convince you if given the chance.
traits.name: tycoon

traits.description: Timmy is strangely hypercoagulating and will bleed much more slowly than most.
traits.name: thickskinned

traits.description: Timmy is strangely hemophilic and tends to bleed much more profusely than others.
traits.name: thinskinned

traits.description: Timmy has trouble expressing themselves until its all too much to bear, whereafter they will have an utter meltdown.
traits.name: schizoid

races.description: A baseline human, mostly unmodified by gene engineering and mostly unchanged by evolutionary pressures on non-Earth planets.
races.name: human

races.description:
A holographic projection operated by a mind located elsewhere. Despite its humanlike appearance, the avatar could belong to a machine persona with frighteningly alien goals.

If the projection is destroyed, its emitter will need a day to reestablish coherence, but the mind itself suffers no permanent harm.
races.name: hologram

races.description: Ratlings (Homo sapiens minimus) are small, loud, hungry and lecherous Abhumans who often serve as snipers in the Astra Militarum, a role at which they excel. Ratlings also serve as cooks for Imperial Guard regiments, a skill they no doubt learned in order to feed their own seemingly bottomless stomachs; and they also have kleptomaniac tendencies, as Commissars report petty theft and illegal gambling rings increase substantially when Ratlings are attached to a platoon, company or regiment.
races.name: ratling

races.description: The dim-witted human sub-species called Ogryns (Homo sapiens gigantus) evolved on high-gravity, low-temperature prison planets. They are huge and unusually stupid for a human subrace, but unquestionably loyal to the Imperium once introduced to the faith of the Imperial Cult. Ogryns are used as the Imperial Guard's shock troops, and for this role, they are commonly outfitted with the Ripper Gun. The Ripper Gun is a weapon simple enough for them to operate, although some feral Ogryn cannot even fathom this device. Ogryn are also frequently used as bodyguards by Imperial Commanders.
races.name: ogryn

races.description: A baseline human, while mostly unmodified by gene engineering and mostly unchanged by evolutionary pressures on non-Earth planets, members of the Cult Mechanicus have usually undergone heavy bionic modifications.
races.name: human (Mechanicus)

races.description:
The Aeldari race has a long and complex spacefaring history, so long in fact that little is known for certain about the course of their physical evolution and early planet-bound existence. The original Aeldari homeworld was destroyed during the catastrophic collapse of the Aeldari civilisation known as the Fall of the Aeldari. The remnants of Aeldari culture that survived the cataclysm preserved much of their species' history in the form of traditional stories, songs and dance. Written records, monuments and visual records were almost completely destroyed except for a few instances where they were taken aboard voidcraft fleeing from the doomed worlds.

As a humanoid race, Aeldari are physically similar to humans, although not entirely identical by any means. They possess longer and cleaner limbs, and fine ascetic features with penetrating and slightly slanted, almond-shaped eyes. Their ears are also slightly pointed, but otherwise they could pass as human at first glance. The most obvious difference between humans and Aeldari can only be seen when they move, for the movements of an Aeldari radiate a subtle grace which is impossible for a human to emulate. This can be seen in even their slightest gestures or the dexterity with which they manipulate small objects.

The Aeldari mind, while similar in general to the human psyche, is far more inclined towards extremes. Because of this, Aeldari are more intelligent but also far more intense than humans. Although an Aeldari and a human can both feel grief or joy, the Aeldari's experience is likely to be far more extreme.
races.name: Eldar

races.description: The Kroot originated on the world of Pech and, though their physiology is humanoid, there is evidence to suggest that the roots of their evolution may be avian in origin. They retain vestigial beaks and have a light, almost hollow bone structure, with four digits on each hand and foot. Their skin is rough with small, barbed spines, similar to the elongated quills on their heads, protruding from various locations on their flesh. Skin pigmentation ranges from earthy brown colours and dappled greens to vibrant oranges and everything in between. Depending on the feeding directions of the Kroot Shapers, the colouration of each kindred can vary quite considerably. It is also common for Kroot from each kindred to have particular tribal markings painted onto their skin. Kroot mature quickly, with their most rapid period of growth occurring in the first ten years of their lives. By the age of twelve they are considered adults and it is not unknown for Kroot to live to over a hundred years old, their skin becoming increasingly pitted and leathery in their last few years of life
races.name: Kroot

races.description:
The Tau are generally shorter than humans, smaller in stature and with less muscle mass and body weight. Every Tau is humanoid in shape, with two arms,[17] two cloven feet, and a single head. Their grey-blue skin is leathery and tough and exudes no moisture, owing to the generally dry conditions of their homeworld. Their faces are flat, wide around the eyes, and their olfactory organs are located inside their mouths. Their eyes can see into the infrared and ultraviolet. Tau eyesight is good, but they focus on distant objects slower than humans. The Tau are not very good in close combat, as they find the whole concept uncivilized.

The Tau has three digits and a single opposable thumb on each hand. The main difference from humans is the bone structure of Tau's lower legs, feet and ankles. Tau have shorter bones of the libia and fibia, but their feet have elongated cuneiform bones and talus and two large central weight-bearing toes. The Tau have eveolved to stand and move without using their heels.[17]
races.name: Tau

races.description: The Vespid are a unique race of insect-like aliens who are members of the T'au Empire. In the T'au Lexicon, they are called "Mal'kor." This derives from the T'au words for insect, "Mal," and air, "Kor." The soldiers of the Imperium of Man often refer to them as "Stingwings." The Vespids' homeworld is a gas giant also called Vespid, three light years to the galactic south of the T'au's D'yanoi Sept.
races.name: Vespid

races.description:
They are bioweapons recreated after Mechanoids by the Anties.

Dreadnaughts are possessed only the most advanced Hives and are stationed at the last lines of defense.

They are equipped with low-angle intercepting systems. Unlike low-angle shields, they deny both incoming and outgoing projectiles.(Dlc) 

If the dreadnaughts are seen on the battlefront, it means child's play is over.
races.name: Anty Dreadnought

races.description:
Anties are genetically engineered beings by a private company to replace dying soldiers on the battle field.

Everything has gone south when the company has let their guard down to celebrate their recent progress. Due to a mistake made by one of the employees, the Anties have been set free from the lab and ended up in space.

Their personalities are gentle by nature, but they were made to know only but war. On each planet they end up, they burn everything down to ash, using themselves as the main source of the fuel.

Anty is hermaphrodite, has no externally exposed reproductive organs, but has both a scrotum and ovaries in the abdomen.

Anty's gender is indicated based on her reproductive system, which was a little more developed prior to consuming the Nutritional jelly.

The average height of common anty ergates and queen ants is 140cm, while soldier ants are 170cm. Depending on needs or the type of hive, it can transform or grow up to 200cm.
races.name: Anty

races.description: A strange and mysterious reptilian race, known for their connection to an even more mysterious tree called the Hist.
races.name: Argonian

races.description: A hardy human-cactus hybrid species able to live in harse conditions.
races.name: cactoid

races.description: A beautiful, semi-reptilian creature with features of a mythical dragon and a human being. They are prized by poachers for their silky, silver hair, and others seek to capture them for their high price at the black markets.
races.name: Dragonian

races.description: A beautiful, semi-reptilian creature with features of a mythical dragon and a human being. They are prized by poachers for their silky, silver hair, and others seek to capture them for their high price at the black markets.

races.name: M7 Mechanised infantry

races.description: A prototype M7 mechanized infantry, equipped with a limited SkyCore unit and SkyMind radio. These units are very strong, powerful war machines and allow digital consciousness to move on battlefields but are subsequently slow and have limited internal storage capacity to them.
races.name: M8 Mechanised infantry

races.description: A lost android, shunned from their transcendant community. The tech used to make them is beyond human comprehension, boasting near unlimited power and requiring little sustinence to operate. They deem all races other than themselves to be somewhat below them and believe that living on a rimworld is a fate worse than death.
races.name: T5 Android

races.description: The most advanced form of android conceivable; this tier is able to efficiently hold the consciousness of any AI uploaded onto it, with advanced locomotive abilities and manipulation; this android vastly suprasses most humans.
races.name: T4 Android

races.description: A Prototype android exclusive to this rimworld; developed by a secret R/D Laboratory, away from the eye of the rest of the planet and cosmos. This android features highly advanced locomotive and motor abilities, perfectly mimicing that of an average human. Although clunky and somewhat slow - this android features a modular component design, allowing for upgrades to be made to current parts at any point.
races.name: T3 Android

races.description: As simple as sentient robotics can get. This design is the bare skeletal amount of components needed to create full autonomous functionality. Obviously not the best but it works well when needed.
races.name: T1 Android

races.description: A somewhat advanced android, capable of almost perfectly storing an AI consciousness and with reasonable levels of motor skills. A good all round android that is uses extensively on glitterworlds for basic maintenance and cleaning.
races.name: T2 Android

races.description: A non feral ghoul, is a decrepit, rotting, zombie-like mutant. Intense and prolonged radiation has ravaged their skin, much of their flesh and in some cases many of their ligaments.
races.name: ghoul

races.description: A non feral glowing ghoul, is a decrepit, rotting, zombie-like mutant. Intense and prolonged radiation has ravaged their skin, much of their flesh and in some cases many of their ligaments. It emits a powerful glow capable of growing plants.
races.name: glowing one

races.description: A curious Ferret race, known for their business acumen.
races.name: Ferrex

races.description: The legacy of a fallen empire, with a distant link to the humanoid races of earth and beyond. Other than the fact that they began to awaken over the past century, no one knows much else about what they are, where they are from or fundamentals behind their technology, which seems to bridge the gap between science and magic.
races.name: forsaken

races.description:
A fairly primitive race, the Gerzee mostly spend their lives foraging for plants, running from large predators, and socializing with the family that have not yet been eaten by those large predators. Though the Gerzee tower in size over most humanoid species, being a fairly small and herbivorous prey species on their home planet means they’ve evolved to run at the first sign of danger. This timid nature and their comparative strength have made them attractive stock for space slavers, and so the Gerzee have just started to be introduced to modern technologies as they deal with these foreign attacks.

With their four eyes on top of their flat head, bulky bodies, and large arms, most humanoid equipment simply doesn’t fit the Gerzee physique. They’re only able to squeeze into some loose or adjustable clothing (e.g. parkas, dusters, masks, flak gear), handle some of the “larger” melee weapons (e.g. spears, horns, swords), and use ranged weapons that don’t require “normal-sized” fingers to pull the trigger (i.e. a minigun).

				

Another technology that surprisingly doesn’t work for the Gerzee is the act of cooking food. However, it’s unclear as to why cooking plants makes them inedible for the Gerzee biology, since slavers don’t mind feeding them cheap hay and glitterworlds have not been interested in researching the answer for such a primitive species.
races.name: Gerzee

races.description: Kijins are ogres who were evolved alikes of humans. Their huge bodies and muscles have shrunk, but the muscles are more dense and stronger. They still have to eat a lot to keep themselves up.
races.name: Kijin

races.description: An all-female race of humans spliced with fox genes. Originally, they were Glitterworld designermates from the planet Aolara, but an internal war forced them to leave their homeworld. Now they are spread among the rim.
races.name: Kurin

races.description: A robust race of fighters, the Logann boast an uncanny regeneration factor.
races.name: Logann

races.description:
A humanoid race living in cities under the sea. Having traits similar to sea creatures, their blood contains substances that can be used for various medical uses.

Descendants of glitterworld explorers who settled in the deep sea, generations of body modifications has led to their current form. Spreading far and wide into the rim, they built many cities and prospered. Until now.
races.name: Moyo

races.description: A subspecies of the Moyo race, usually babies born after a Moyo is fertilized by a creature infected with the deep-sea virus. And because the symbiotic virus affects, most of them have strange personalities, but not intrinsically bad.
races.name: Red Moyo

races.description: It is a human like a rodent gene. Although the origin is unknown, it is a monarchy society based on agricultural society. There are more female objects than males, and it is difficult to distinguish the gender of the object when viewed from the outside.
races.name: Ratkin

races.description: It is a human like a rodent gene. Although the origin is unknown, it is a monarchy society based on agricultural society. There are more female objects than males, and it is difficult to distinguish the gender of the object when viewed from the outside.

races.description: The mysterious horned and feathered humanoid found on some rim worlds, Oni are often sought out by Glitterworlds for their beauty as a sort of exotic pet. Worse still some are kept as livestock for their feathers, pelts and horns, all having pratical and decorative uses. Oni live in temperate areas and rarely employ clothing due to the uncomfortable sensation on their feathered bodies.
races.name: Oni

races.description: The ancient ancestors of the current Oni that can be found on some rim worlds. They have been mysteriously appearing with no traceable origins, but their descendant race welcomes them into their tribes without question.
races.name: Ancestral Oni

races.description: A baseline orassan, mostly unmodified by gene engineering and mostly unchanged by evolutionary pressures on non-Orassia planets. A mammalian humanoid feline race. Evolving in cold caves and life on space ships make it so they don't mind the dark or being inside for long periods of time.
races.name: orassan

races.description: A hybrid with DNA from a human and an orassan. Typically created through careful genetic engineering in a lab, or the "natural" way from individuals with closely regulated gene mods, these hybrids combine some of the best traits from their parent species. The particular traits and physical characteristics that are being inherited are typically chosen by the parents having the child, but they almost always have two feline ears and a feline tail, both with fur sharing the same color as the hair on their head.
races.name: neko
